AB  - Background: Previous studies showed that anger, rather than sadness, created automatic intergroup bias in a minimal group context.
   Methods: The current research reports a single study (N=99) aiming to replicate this finding and further to test whether the intergroup bias manifests as in group favoritism, outgroup derogation, or both.
